title: Whole Foods Recalls Frozen Pizza Products Due to Misbranding
summary: WASHINGTON, Jan. 25, 2016 Whole Foods/North Atlantic Kitchens, an Everett, Mass. establishment, is recalling approximately 73,898 pounds of pepperoni pizza products due to misbranding, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The product is labeled as containing uncured beef...
